@startuml arqDespliegue

skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam nodeBorderThickness 1.5
skinparam arrowThickness 1.2
skinparam arrowColor #444444
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF

skinparam node {
  BackgroundColor #dce8f5
  BorderColor     #2d6a9f
}

skinparam database {
  BackgroundColor #d5ecd4
  BorderColor     #2e7d32
}

skinparam cloud {
  BackgroundColor #efefef
  BorderColor     #888888
}

title Diagrama de despliegue

node "Navegador del usuario" as Browser {
  artifact "Aplicación cliente\n(Next.js hydration)" as Client
}

node "Servidor VPS (Ubuntu)" as VPS {
  node "Red Docker interna" as Docker {
    node "Contenedor Next.js\n(Node.js 20, puerto 3000)" as NextJS {
      artifact "Páginas RSC + Server Actions" as RSC
      artifact "Rutas API\n(/api/auth, webhooks)" as API
    }
    database "Contenedor PostgreSQL 16\n(sin exposición exterior)" as PG
  }
  artifact "CI/CD (GitHub Actions)" as CICD
}

cloud "Microsoft 365" as M365 {
  node "Entra ID\n(OAuth 2.0/OIDC)" as EntraID
  node "Graph API\n(calendario, Teams)" as Graph
}

cloud "Resend" as ResendCloud {
  node "API de email" as Resend
}

Browser -down-> NextJS  : HTTPS / nginx (puerto 443)
NextJS  -down-> PG      : Drizzle ORM (red interna)
NextJS  -right-> EntraID : SSO (OAuth 2.0/OIDC)
NextJS  -right-> Graph   : Bearer token
NextJS  -right-> Resend  : API key (email visitantes)
CICD   -up-> NextJS      : despliegue continuo

note right of Docker
  Ambos contenedores comparten
  la red interna Docker.
  PostgreSQL no está expuesto
  al exterior.
end note

@enduml
